The White House Press Secretary released a statement congratulating the Iranian people on the inauguration of President Hassan Rouhani. The statement highlights the hope that the new Iranian government will listen to the will of the voters and make choices that improve the lives of the Iranian people. It also emphasizes the opportunity for Iran to address the international community's concerns about its nuclear program, stating that if the new government engages seriously and meets its obligations, the United States is willing to be a partner in finding a peaceful solution.